Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the potatoes into a low sided wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{3%tbsp}, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

== Walnut Parsley Pesto ==

Finely chop the @walnuts{20}(finely chopped) and pop them into a #bowl{}. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped, stalks and all). Pop the parsley into the bowl with the walnuts and add the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and @olive oil{3%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix together.

> Add a little more olive oil if you want it to be more of a drizzly consistency.

== Tomato Rocket Salad ==

Put the @red wine vinegar{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{} with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix together with a #fork{}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop them in the bowl with the dressing. Mix together, then set aside.

> You'll add the rocket to the dressing at the end.

== Hake ==

Put the @plain flour{16%g} on a #plate{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Pat the @hake fillets{2} dry with some #kitchen paper{}, then pop it on the plate with the flour and turn so the whole fillet is coated in the seasoned flour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw fish.

When the potatoes are 5 mins from being cooked, heat a glug of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once the oil is hot, lay the fish in the pan and fry until golden all over, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque all the way through.

Remove the pan from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the tomatoes and toss together. Serve the fish with the roast potatoes and salad alongside. Spoon the homemade pesto on top of the fish and enjoy!